<text xml:lang="ta">
  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <p xml:id="PN372-intro">tiṇai, vākai. maṟakkaḷavēḷvi. avaṉai māṅkuṭikiḻār (māta<gap quantity="4" reason="lost" unit="character"/> kakiḻār)
      </p>
      <p xml:lang="en">  
      </p>
    </div>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="PN372">
<l>vicipiṇit taṭāri vimmeṉa voṟṟi</l>
<l>yētti vanta tellā muḻutta</l>
<l>vilaṅkuvā ḷaviroḷi valampaṭa miṉṉik</l>
<l>kaṇaittuḷi poḻinta kaṇkūṭu pācaṟaip</l>
<l>poruntāt tevva rarintatalai yaṭuppiṟ</l>
<l>kūviḷa viṟaki ṉākkuvari nuṭaṅka</l>
<l>lāṉā maṇṭai vaṉṉiyan tuṭuppi</l>
<l>ṉīṉā vēṇmā ḷiṭantuḻan taṭṭa</l>
<l>māmaṟi piṇṭam vāluva ṉēnta</l>
<l>vatuvai viḻaviṟ putuvōrk kellām</l>
<l>vevvāyp peyta pūtanīr cālkeṉap</l>
<l>pulavukkaḷam poliya vēṭṭōyniṉ</l>
<l>ṉilavuttika ḻāra mukakkuva meṉavē.</l>
</lg>
<lg xml:lang="en">
<l corresp="1">Loudly beating the Taṭāri drum tied with straps </l>
<l corresp="2ab">[we] came, praising [you], </l>
<l corresp="4">in the war camp that joins the area where arrows had flown as [rain] drops, </l>
<l corresp="3">with the shining light of shining swords flashing victorioulsly, </l>
<l corresp="2cd">	all at once(?), </l>
<l corresp="13">thinking that we will draw pearl-strings glimmering of moonlight, </l>
<l corresp="12">from you who sacrificed so that the flesh-reeking battle field flourishes, </l>
<l corresp="11">saying “let you Bhūtas be many into whose red mouths is poured </l>
<l corresp="10">all [given to] newcomers at wedding feasts, </l>
<l corresp="9">when the cook offers balls of dark kid </l>
<l corresp="8">that was cooked, stirring the place, by a Vēṇmāḷ woman who had not given birth, </l>
<l corresp="7">with a Vaṉṉi-wooden ladle into unending bowls, </l>
<l corresp="5">on the fireplace [made] of the cut-off heads of uncouth enemies </l>
<l corresp="6">kindling(?) firewood of Bael, swaying in lines. </l>
</lg>
    </div>
